1) Confirm you won't cannibalize. For example, entering interview questions sounds like a great idea, but we're already doing that on JPAY. Considering that a lot of students don't even enter questions on JPAY, I suggest making sure questions are entered only on one platform to increase amount of responses in one place.
2) With respect to interview questions, I think students should be mandated to enter their interview questions from interviews obtained from on-campus sources on JPAY. I realize this may sound like overreach, but the more questions answered, the better students can prepare and knock the interview out of the park. Also, I think this can help us gain a competitive advantage against our peer schools by having an internal repository of interview questions.
3) Don't charge for the app. Students are already paying an exorbitant amount for an MBA--I could give you a long list of where I think Johnson could cut costs and use those savings to pay for the app.
